errors.prescription:
1. Use the fully qualified name (e.g., System.Threading.Timer instead of Timer).
2. Add a using alias: using MyTimer = System.Threading.Timer;
3. Remove one of the conflicting 'using' directives if it's not needed.

errors.codeBlock:
// BEFORE (wrong)
using System.Threading;
using System.Timers;

Timer t = new Timer(); // CS0104: ambiguous

// AFTER (correct — fully qualified)
System.Threading.Timer t = new System.Threading.Timer(callback, null, 0, 1000);

// AFTER (correct — alias)
using ThreadTimer = System.Threading.Timer;
ThreadTimer t = new ThreadTimer(callback, null, 0, 1000);

// BEFORE (wrong)
var arr = new[] { 1, "two", 3.0 }; // CS0826

// AFTER (correct)
object[] arr = new object[] { 1, "two", 3.0 };

// BEFORE (wrong)
var result = flag ? new Cat() : new Dog(); // CS0173 if no common base

// AFTER (correct)
Animal result = flag ? (Animal)new Cat() : new Dog();

// BEFORE (SA1101)
Name = "test";

// AFTER (correct)
this.Name = "test";

